      <div xml:id="NA123-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu talaivaṉ ciṟaippuṟamākat (EN, ER, ET, EV: ciṟaippuṟattāṉākat) tōḻi talaivikku uraippāḷāyc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said as one who is talking to HER while HE was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA123">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uraiyāy vāḻi tōḻi yiruṅkaḻi</l>
<l>            yiraiyār kuruki ṉiraippaṟait toḻuti</l>
<l>            vāṅkumaṭaṟ kuṭampait tūṅkiruṭ ṭuvaṉṟum</l>
<l>            peṇṇai yōṅkiya veṇmaṇaṟ paṭappaik</l>
<l>            kāṉa lāyamoṭu kālaik kuṟṟa </l>
<l>            kaṭkama ḻalara taṇṇaṟuṅ kāvi</l>
<l>            yampakai neṟittaḻai yaṇipeṟat taii</l>
<l>            varipuṉai ciṟṟiṟ pariciṟan tōṭip</l>
<l>            pulavuttirai yutaitta koṭuntāṭ kaṇṭaṟ</l>
<l>            cērppē rīraḷai yalavaṟ pārkkuñ </l>
<l>            ciṟuviḷai yāṭalu maḻuṅka</l>
<l>            niṉakkuperun tuyara mākiya nōyē.</l>

    </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent3">You don't talk, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent4">of the pain that has become a great misery for you</l>
<l rend="indent3">so that even playing a little is spoiled:</l>
<l>when [you] peer out for crabs with wet holes, rising on the shore</l>
<l rend="indent">of mangroves with bent trunks, kicked by the fish-reeking waves,</l>
<l>when [you]<note place="foot">In the original an impersonal construction is possible: <term xml:lang="ta">taii</term> ... <term xml:lang="ta">ōṭi</term> ... <term xml:lang="ta">pārkkum</term> ... <term xml:lang="ta">āṭal</term>, "the playing that knits ... runs ... [and] peers".</note> run, faster in motion, to the small houses adorned with lines,</l>
<l>when [you] knit together,</l>
<l rend="indent">to get a decoration, foliage [and] calyxes, in pretty contrast,</l>
<l rend="indent">of the cool fragrant blue waterlily with blossoms fragrant of nectar,</l>
<l rend="indent">plucked in the morning with the companions in the seashore grove</l>
<l rend="indent2">in the garden of white sand grown high with palmyra palms,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the hanging darkness of the nests on the bent stems is filled up</l>
<l rend="indent3">by a multitude of wings in a row of herons feeding on prey</l>
<l rend="indent4">from the dark backwaters.</l>
        </lg>
